## Law 8 — `withLoading` vs `withPageLoading`: Global vs Content-Area

**Source**: `src/hooks/layout/useLoading.ts`

There are **two independent loading counter systems**. Using the wrong one shows the wrong UI layer.

| API | Counter | UI effect | Typical use |
|---|---|---|---|
| `loadingStart()` / `loadingDone()` | `layoutStore.loadingCount` | Full-screen overlay (covers entire layout) | App init, auth check, critical global operations |
| `withLoading(fn)` | same | Full-screen overlay (auto-paired) | Any async op needing full-screen block |
| `pageLoadingStart()` / `pageLoadingDone()` | `layoutStore.pageLoadingCount` | Content-area skeleton (inside LayoutAdmin) | Route data fetching, page-level API calls |
| `withPageLoading(fn)` | same | Content-area skeleton (auto-paired) | Preferred pattern for page data loading |

**REQUIRED — Prefer auto-paired wrappers** (avoids missing `finally`):

```typescript
const { withLoading, withPageLoading } = useLoading()

// ✅ Full-screen block (global auth, critical init)
const result = await withLoading(async () => {
  return await initializeApp()
})

// ✅ Content-area skeleton (page data fetch — MOST COMMON)
const data = await withPageLoading(async () => {
  return await fetchPageData()
})
```

**FORBIDDEN — Manual start/done without finally protection:**
```typescript
// ❌ FORBIDDEN: loadingDone() may never be called if the await throws
const { pageLoadingStart, pageLoadingDone } = useLoading()
pageLoadingStart()
const data = await fetchData() // if this throws, done() is never called → stuck spinner
pageLoadingDone()
```

**Decision rule:**
- Route guard / app bootstrap → `withLoading`
- Page `onMounted` data fetch / table refresh → `withPageLoading`
